'3:8': [
{sup:"1a", word:"furnishings", vrefs:"Num. 4:15, 28, 33", lines:["The Tabernacle of the Testimony with all its furnishings and the altar (vv. {Num3:25|25}-{Num3:26|26}, {Num3:31|31}, {Num3:36|36}-{Num3:37|37}), to which the priests ministered, are types of Christ in all His rich aspects, whom the New Testament believers minister to others ({Eph3:8|Eph. 3:8}; {2Co3:3|2&nbsp;Cor. 3:3}; {1Ti4:6|1&nbsp;Tim. 4:6}). The altar, signifying the cross ({Heb13:10|Heb. 13:10}), refers to Christ&rsquo;s redemption, and the tabernacle refers to Christ as the embodiment of God ({Col2:9|Col. 2:9}), through whom God dwells among men ({Joh1:14|John 1:14}) and through whom men can enter into God to enjoy all that He is ({Joh14:2|John 14:2}, {Joh14:6|6}, {Joh14:20|20}). To minister is to serve, and to serve is to supply people by ministering to them. The New Testament believers serve others the cross of Christ for redemption ({1Co1:23|1&nbsp;Cor. 1:23}; {1Co2:2|2:2}) and the riches of Christ for the life supply ({Eph3:8|Eph. 3:8}; {Col1:27|Col. 1:27}-{Col1:28|28})."]},
],
