'3:17': [
{sup:1, word:"sons", lines:["God gave Jacob twelve sons so that there could be twelve tribes encamped around the tabernacle, three tribes on each of the four sides ({Num2|ch. 2}). God gave Levi three sons to camp around three sides of the tabernacle in the midst of the four camps ({Num2:17|2:17})&mdash;the Gershonites on the west ({Num3:23|v. 23}), the Kohathites on the south ({Num3:29|v. 29}), and the sons of Merari on the north ({Num3:35|v. 35}). Moses, Aaron, and Aaron&rsquo;s sons camped on the east, in front of the tabernacle ({Num3:38|v. 38}). Only God could provide the persons needed to have such an array. None of those involved in this array was hired; all were born. Likewise, the building up of the Body of Christ has nothing to do with hired persons; it is altogether a matter of the divine life through the divine birth and is therefore organic ({Eph4:11|Eph. 4:11}-{Eph4:16|16})."]},
{sup:"a", word:"Gershon", vrefs:"Gen. 46:11; Exo. 6:16; Num. 26:57; 1&nbsp;Chron. 6:1, 16; 23:6"},
],
