'10:31': [
{sup:1, word:"Moses", lines:["Lit., he."]},
{sup:2, word:"eyes", lines:["Moses thought that his father-in-law would be a great help, but God&rsquo;s sovereignty would not allow any man to come in. Thus, Moses and the children of Israel had to put their trust in the Lord. This account of Moses&rsquo; trusting in man is inserted here to compare man&rsquo;s leading with the leading of the Ark in the subsequent verses."]},
],
'10:33': [
{sup:"a", word:"mountain", vrefs:"Exo. 3:1"},
{sup:"1b", word:"Ark", vrefs:"Josh. 3:3-4, 6; cf. Num. 14:44; Exo. 25:16; Deut. 10:2", lines:["God&rsquo;s guidance to His people in a general way was by the cloud and the trumpets ({Num9:15|9:15}&mdash;{Num10:10|10:10}), whereas His leading of His people in a particular way was through the Ark (vv. {Num10:33|33}-{Num10:36|36}), a type of the crucified and resurrected Christ in His resurrection. Hence, the unique Leader of God&rsquo;s people is not any man (cf. vv. {Num10:29|29}-{Num10:32|32}) but is the crucified and resurrected Christ ({Mat23:10|Matt. 23:10}). He is the Leader, and He leads us to the proper place of rest on the long and rugged journey of the Christian life ({Heb4:8|Heb. 4:8}-{Heb4:9|9} and {Heb4:8^1|notes}).","The leading of the Ark of the Covenant indicates that the leading of Christ is faithful, according to a covenant. God made a covenant with Abraham and his descendants to bring them into the good land ({Gen17:1|Gen. 17:1}-{Gen17:8|8}; cf. {Exo23:20^1|note 20<sup>1</sup>} in {Exo23|Exo. 23}). Eventually, God&rsquo;s covenant was placed in the Ark; thus, the Ark was called the Ark of the Covenant. Hence, the Christ who leads us into a resting place is the Christ of the covenant, the Christ of God&rsquo;s faithfulness (cf. {2Co1:19|2&nbsp;Cor. 1:19}-{2Co1:20|20})."]},
{sup:"c", word:"resting", vrefs:"Deut. 1:33; Psa. 132:8; Jer. 31:2"},
],
