'20:8': [
{sup:"a", word:"rod", vrefs:"Exo. 17:5"},
{sup:"1b", word:"rock", vrefs:"Exo. 17:6", lines:["The rock in this chapter typifies the crucified and resurrected Christ ({1Co10:4|1&nbsp;Cor. 10:4b}), and the water that flowed from the rock typifies the Spirit ({1Co10:4|1&nbsp;Cor. 10:4a}) as the living water that flowed out of the crucified Christ ({Joh19:34|John 19:34} and {Joh19:34^1|note}). In {Exo17|Exo. 17} Moses struck the rock with his rod, and water flowed out for the people to drink (see notes {Exo17:6^2|6<sup>2</sup>} and {Exo17:6^3|6<sup>3</sup>} in {Exo17|Exo. 17}). According to Paul&rsquo;s word in {1Co10:4|1&nbsp;Cor. 10:4} (see {1Co10:4^2|note 4<sup>2</sup>} there), this rock was a spiritual rock that followed God&rsquo;s people in their journey through the wilderness. This signifies that Christ has been crucified to become a rock that follows His people. This following rock is the resurrected Christ as the life-giving Spirit ({1Co15:45|1&nbsp;Cor. 15:45}), who is always with the church to supply His believers with the water of life.","Since Christ has been crucified and the Spirit has been given, there is no need for Christ to be crucified again, i.e., no need to strike the rock again, that the living water may flow. In God&rsquo;s economy Christ should be crucified only once ({Heb7:27|Heb. 7:27}; {Heb9:26|9:26}-{Heb9:28|28a}). To receive the living water from the crucified Christ, we need only to &ldquo;take the rod&rdquo; and &ldquo;speak to the rock.&rdquo; To take the rod is to identify with Christ in His death and apply the death of Christ to ourselves and our situation. To speak to the rock is to speak a direct word to Christ as the smitten rock, asking Him to give us the Spirit of life (cf. {Joh4:10|John 4:10}) based on the fact that the Spirit has already been given. If we apply the death of Christ to ourselves and ask Christ in faith to give us the Spirit, we will receive the living Spirit as the bountiful supply of life ({Phi1:19|Phil. 1:19})."]},
{sup:"c", word:"drink", vrefs:"cf. John 4:14"},
],
